lonithus] According to Methodius, a fourth son of Noah, who was supposed to have invented astronomy: cp. Fabri· cius, Codex pseudepigraphus Vet. Test, i. 271.

non ab homine] From Gal. i. 12.

Zoroastes] Cp. Gervas. Tilb., Otia Impen, i. 20: “Zoro- ester alio nomine Cham filius Noae vocabatur. ”

immundorum servitor spirituum] Cp. Matt. x. 1.

sauctus Enoch] Cp. Eccli. xliv. 16: “Enoch . . . trans· latus est in Paradisum ut det gentibus poenitentiam.”

raptus in ecstasi] Cp. 2 Cor. xii. 4.

liber Logostilios] Inglis supposed this to refer to the lost Logistoricus of Varro.
